Error: abstract var 'SHAPE' cannot use an allocation count
   ╭─[ tests/golden/fixtures/syntax-abstract-var-err-count/input.k65:1:1 ]
   │
 1 │ ╭─▶ abstract var SHAPE[
   ┆ ┆   
 3 │ ├─▶ ] * 4
   │ │           
   │ ╰─────────── allocation count on abstract var
   │     
   │     Help: remove `* count` from 'SHAPE'; use `SHAPE:sizeof * count` in expressions when you need scaled layout math
   │     
   │     Note: `* count` reserves repeated storage for real vars. Abstract vars reserve no storage, so repetition belongs at the use site as arithmetic.
